description:
Beautiful Upper West Side apartment on third floor of prewar walk-up building set against a very quiet and tranquil courtyard. Light-filled with high ceilings and eclectic furnishings. Queen in bedroom and fold out sofa with enclosed blow up mattress in living room. 

One of the best locations in New York. Nearly unlimited restaurants and coffee shops. Less than 5 minute walk to two different subway lines (A/C and 1/2/3). Within blocks of Central Park, Riverside Park, and Columbia University.

hosts.about: Born and raised in Virginia, I live in New York and travel quite a bit for work and pleasure. I work on issues related to sustainable forestry, farming, and natural resource management. I enjoy reading, writing fiction, and learning guitar. I try to spend as much time as possible at a beautiful farm in Virginia. It is listed for rent on AirBnb--take a look!

house_rules:

• Not suitable for pets
• No smoking

There are many places to go. Apartment is clean and cozy. I definitely recommend you to visit Charle's apartment if you want to make your trip to New York amazing.
